# Mailbox Store -- Canonical Message Architecture Refactor

## Problem

The store has 4 overlapping data structures for messages:

- `messages` (reactive array) -- current folder list
- `threadMessages` (reactive object) -- conversation thread cache
- `memoryCache` (Map) -- LRU body content cache
- `messageIndex` (reactive object) -- O(1) UID lookup index

The same message can exist as 3 different objects simultaneously. This causes:
- State sync bugs (marking one copy read doesn't update others)
- Complex merge/dedup logic (`smartMergeMessages`, `loadConversationMessagesBackground`)
- Index rebuilds on every fetch (`rebuildMessageIndex`)
- Cache invalidation complexity (30 `memoryCache` references)

## Target Architecture

One canonical message store. A message exists once in memory.

```
messagesByKey: reactive(new Map())     // folder:uid -> message object
folderViews:   reactive(new Map())     // folder -> ordered key[]
conversationKeys: reactive(new Map())  // convId -> ordered key[]
```

All views store only keys. UI resolves via `messagesByKey.get(key)`.

## Core Helper -- `upsertMessage`

All message data enters the store through a single function:

```js
function upsertMessage(msg, folder = null) {
  const f = folder || msg.folder || currentFolder.value
  const key = `${f}:${Number(msg.uid)}`
  const existing = messagesByKey.get(key)
  if (existing) {
    // Update changed fields on the existing object (preserves Vue reactivity reference)
    for (const [k, v] of Object.entries(msg)) {
      if (existing[k] !== v) existing[k] = v
    }
  } else {
    messagesByKey.set(key, { ...msg, folder: f })
  }
  return key
}
```

Used by: fetch responses, WebSocket events, batch operations, body fetches.

## Migration Steps

Each step is independently deployable and testable.

### Step 1 -- Add `messagesByKey` + `upsertMessage` (low risk, ~15 min)

- Add `const messagesByKey = reactive(new Map())`
- Add `upsertMessage()` helper (canonical write path from day one)
- After each existing `rebuildMessageIndex()` call, also upsert into `messagesByKey`
- Both old and new systems coexist with same data
- **Risk: zero.** Nothing reads from the new map yet.
- **Key principle:** Start with the canonical write path immediately. Don't dual-populate `rebuildMessageIndex` -- that creates throwaway coupling.

### Step 2 -- Route lookups, delete `messageIndex` (~30 min)

- `findMessageByUid()` reads from `messagesByKey` (direct key lookup)
- All 8 `rebuildMessageIndex()` call sites become `upsertMessage()` loops
- Delete `messageIndex` ref and `rebuildMessageIndex()` function
- **Risk: low.** Same logic, different backing structure. All internal.

### Step 3 -- Merge `memoryCache` into `messagesByKey` (~20 min)

- Body fetches write `body_html`/`body_text` directly onto canonical objects via `upsertMessage` or direct field assignment
- "Has body?" check: `messagesByKey.get(key)?.body_html != null`
- Delete: `memoryCache`, `MEMORY_CACHE_MAX`, `clearMemoryCache()`, `renameFolderInCache()`, `clearFolderFromCache()`
- **Eviction must be view-aware** (see eviction rules below)
- **Risk: medium.** LRU eviction changes. Test body caching thoroughly.

### Step 4 -- Add `folderViews`, keep `messages` as computed (~45 min)

- Add `const folderViews = reactive(new Map())` -- folder name to ordered `folder:uid` key arrays
- `messages` becomes computed alias:
  ```js
  const messages = computed(() =>
    (folderViews.get(currentFolder.value) || [])
      .map(k => messagesByKey.get(k))
      .filter(Boolean)
  )
  ```
- **Zero external file changes** -- all 13 consumer files keep reading `mailbox.messages`
- `smartMergeMessages()` becomes a simple `upsertMessage` loop (no array diffing)
- Folder switching instant for previously visited folders (view already populated)
- **Performance:** The computed must depend only on `currentFolder` and the key array reference, not on individual message object fields. The existing `conversationsRefreshTrigger` handles conversation recomputation separately.
- **Risk: medium.** Pivotal step. The computed derivation must stay performant.

### Step 5 -- Replace `threadMessages` with `conversationKeys` (~60 min)

- Add `const conversationKeys = reactive(new Map())` -- convId to `folder:uid` key arrays
- `getConversationMessages(convId)` becomes:
  ```js
  conversationKeys.get(convId)?.map(k => messagesByKey.get(k)).filter(Boolean)
  ```
- `fetchThreadMessages()` populates `conversationKeys` and upserts into `messagesByKey`
- **Keys must be sorted by timestamp** at storage time:
  ```js
  keys.sort((a, b) => messagesByKey.get(b)?.timestamp - messagesByKey.get(a)?.timestamp)
  conversationKeys.set(convId, keys)
  ```
  Current thread code explicitly sorts (mailbox.js ~line 2140) -- this guarantee must survive the migration.
- Simplify `useConversationGrouping.js` -- no more thread merge/dedup from `threadMessagesMap`
- `EmailList.vue` lines ~1519-1523: change `threadMessages` invalidation to `conversationKeys.delete(id)`
- `loadConversationMessagesBackground()` simplifies: fetch, upsert, store keys
- `prefetchThreadBodies()` simplifies: fetch and write onto existing canonical objects
- **Risk: highest.** Conversation grouping is the most complex consumer. Test thoroughly.

### Step 6 -- Cleanup (~15 min)

Delete:
- `messageIndex` ref
- `rebuildMessageIndex()` function (8 call sites)
- `memoryCache` Map and all helpers (`clearMemoryCache`, `renameFolderInCache`, `clearFolderFromCache`)
- `threadMessages` ref
- `smartMergeMessages()` function
- `prefetchThreadBodies()` in old form

**Estimated net reduction: 600-900 lines.**

## Eviction Rules

Never evict messages currently visible. Build a protected set:

```js
const protectedKeys = new Set([
  ...(folderViews.get(currentFolder.value) || []),
  ...(currentMessage.value?.conversationKey
    ? (conversationKeys.get(currentMessage.value.conversationKey) || [])
    : []),
])
```

Only keys NOT in `protectedKeys` are eligible for eviction. Simple size cap (e.g., 2000 entries) with sweep of unprotected keys when exceeded.

This prevents:
- Thread breakage (conversation key pointing to evicted message)
- Current view corruption
- Open message disappearing

## Fetch Token Protection

The existing `fetchMessagesToken` protects against folder-switch race conditions. With `folderViews`, a late-arriving response for folder A writing into `folderViews['A']` while viewing folder B is safe (doesn't affect current view). The risk is two fetches for the **same** folder overlapping. Solutions:
- Per-folder token (or last-requested timestamp per folder)
- The existing single token already covers most cases since `fetchMessages` sets `currentFolder` before awaiting

## WebSocket Integration Update (after Step 4)

In `useMailSyncIntegration.js`, update handlers to use canonical store:

```
WebSocket event arrives
    |
    v
upsertMessage() into messagesByKey
    |
    v
update folderViews[folder] (add/remove key)
    |
    v
if folder === currentFolder -> UI updates instantly
if folder !== currentFolder -> view is pre-warmed for next switch
    |
    v
pendingFlags protects optimistic state
conversationsRefreshTrigger bumps computed
```

Non-current folder views get pre-warmed by WebSocket events, enabling instant folder switching.

## What Stays Unchanged

- `pendingFlags` system (orthogonal concern)
- `fetchMessagesToken` cancellation (still needed)
- `conversationsRefreshTrigger` reactivity pattern (still needed for Vue computed)
- All API endpoints and payloads
- `selectedMessages` composite key system
- `pagination`, `loading`, `bulkProgress`
- `pinnedEmails`
- All 13 external consumer files (thanks to `messages` computed alias)

## Vue Reactivity Note

`Map` mutations don't auto-trigger computed watchers:
```js
messagesByKey.get(key).seen = true  // won't trigger computed re-eval
```
Solution: bump `conversationsRefreshTrigger++` after mutations (already used throughout the store). The `messages` computed should depend only on `currentFolder` and key array references, not on message object fields.

